- Place scripts in `~/bin` or `~/.local/bin`. Make them **POSIX sh** when possible.
- Create user **systemd** units under `~/.config/systemd/user/`. Provide templates for `eww.service`, `keyd.service` etc. Use `systemctl --user`.
- Cross-distro patterns:
  - Package manager detection only in a one-off install script; at runtime use generic tools (`xdg-open`, `update-alternatives` neutral commands).
